label: AB_oI4_44_a_b-001
title: High-pressure GaAs Structure
comments: This is a high-pressure phase of GaAs, stable above 24 GPa. The experimental data used here was taken at a pressure of 28.1 GPa. Without loss of generality we can take $z_{1}=0$. When $a=b$ and $z_{2}=z_{1}+1/4$ this structure becomes the \href{current_web_home_dir/A_tI4_141_a-001}{$\beta$-Sn (A5)} structure.
